1
00:00:15,248 --> 00:00:16,408
[ Thunder crashes ]

2
00:00:16,516 --> 00:00:18,746
♪ It's raining ♪

3
00:00:18,852 --> 00:00:21,548
♪ It's pouring ♪

4
00:00:21,654 --> 00:00:25,988
♪ The old man is snoring ♪

5
00:00:26,092 --> 00:00:30,324
♪ He went to bed
and bumped his head ♪

6
00:00:30,430 --> 00:00:33,831
♪ He couldn't get up
in the morning ♪

7
00:00:33,933 --> 00:00:38,165
CARI: They say that those
who fail to learn from their past

8
00:00:38,271 --> 00:00:40,603
are destined to repeat it.

9
00:00:40,707 --> 00:00:43,540
This story begins well before my time,

10
00:00:43,643 --> 00:00:47,010
in a place called Perseverance.

11
00:00:47,113 --> 00:00:51,049
In all, three generations
would come to tell the tale.

12
00:00:51,151 --> 00:00:55,053
Three generations
would come to fear the rain.

13
00:00:55,155 --> 00:00:57,248
[ Thunder crashes ]

14
00:01:11,137 --> 00:01:13,731
[ Woman vocalizing ]

15
00:01:35,061 --> 00:01:37,052
Please, whoever you are...

16
00:01:37,163 --> 00:01:39,427
Please, just let me go.

17
00:01:39,532 --> 00:01:41,591
[ Panting ]

18
00:01:47,974 --> 00:01:50,033
What do you want?

19
00:02:09,963 --> 00:02:12,830
[ Screaming ]

20
00:02:31,518 --> 00:02:34,919
[ indistinct chanting ]

21
00:02:44,998 --> 00:02:47,023
[ indistinct chanting ]

22
00:03:25,772 --> 00:03:27,239
[ Sighs ]

23
00:03:27,340 --> 00:03:29,137
[ inhales deeply ]

24
00:03:29,242 --> 00:03:31,335
Ahh.

25
00:03:34,380 --> 00:03:36,871
[ Sniffles ]

26
00:03:42,589 --> 00:03:45,558
One more week without rain...

27
00:03:45,658 --> 00:03:48,058
and we'll all be dead.

28
00:03:51,831 --> 00:03:53,298
Pa...

29
00:03:54,934 --> 00:03:56,299
Ain't that Simon Wheeler?

30
00:04:01,774 --> 00:04:03,605
Daniel, no! Daniel!

31
00:04:08,114 --> 00:04:10,912
Help me, please.
Don't let it get me.

32
00:04:11,017 --> 00:04:11,881
Who?

33
00:04:11,985 --> 00:04:13,953
The hat.

34
00:04:28,368 --> 00:04:31,269
You mind when I'm talking to you!

35
00:04:31,437 --> 00:04:32,927
Now, you go home
and look after your sister!

36
00:04:33,039 --> 00:04:34,597
Go on!

37
00:04:35,341 --> 00:04:36,740
Go!

38
00:04:41,414 --> 00:04:43,109
[ Whimpers ]

39
00:04:44,284 --> 00:04:46,343
I want my pa.

40
00:04:48,921 --> 00:04:51,947
I know your father, boy.

41
00:05:11,344 --> 00:05:13,710
[ Leaves rustling ]

42
00:05:47,213 --> 00:05:50,307
[ Girl screams ]

43
00:05:57,357 --> 00:05:59,587
[ Wood creaking ]

44
00:06:15,675 --> 00:06:19,202
[ Coughing ]

45
00:06:27,920 --> 00:06:29,979
[ Coughing continues ]

46
00:06:38,931 --> 00:06:41,024
[ Knock on door ]

47
00:06:43,870 --> 00:06:45,565
[ Knock on door ]

48
00:06:51,544 --> 00:06:53,842
DELL: Open up, ladies!

49
00:06:57,116 --> 00:06:58,105
Jenny...

50
00:06:59,452 --> 00:07:00,885
...take the money.

51
00:07:06,592 --> 00:07:10,119
DELL: You got to pay to stay, ladies!

52
00:07:21,574 --> 00:07:23,439
[ Hinges creak ]

53
00:07:23,543 --> 00:07:25,636
You got the rent?

54
00:07:43,229 --> 00:07:45,424
No!

55
00:07:45,531 --> 00:07:46,964
I want that.

56
00:07:47,066 --> 00:07:47,725
[ Gun cocks ]

57
00:07:47,834 --> 00:07:49,768
You let my child go.

58
00:07:55,041 --> 00:07:57,532
Brenda, give him the water.

59
00:07:57,743 --> 00:07:59,142
But it's all we have.

60
00:07:59,645 --> 00:08:01,772
Give him the water.

61
00:08:09,655 --> 00:08:12,783
Here, boy. Take this.

62
00:08:21,634 --> 00:08:23,033
Dell.

63
00:08:24,437 --> 00:08:27,929
He was talking crazy things.

64
00:08:28,040 --> 00:08:30,508
I didn't have no choice.

65
00:08:30,610 --> 00:08:34,671
I had to think of the kids.
You understand?

66
00:08:35,448 --> 00:08:37,643
He knows you're here, Jean.

67
00:08:37,750 --> 00:08:39,980
If I was you, I'd pack my things
and get back home

68
00:08:40,086 --> 00:08:42,554
before he sends the sheriff.

69
00:08:42,655 --> 00:08:45,647
You'll never make it out of town.

70
00:08:47,727 --> 00:08:49,592
[ Coughs ]

71
00:08:57,503 --> 00:09:01,200
Mama, why are all
the grown-ups sick?

72
00:09:01,307 --> 00:09:04,299
[ Telephone ringing ]

73
00:09:13,085 --> 00:09:14,643
No, mama, please!

74
00:09:14,820 --> 00:09:16,788
[ Ringing continues ]

75
00:09:24,096 --> 00:09:24,994
JENNY: Daddy?

76
00:09:25,097 --> 00:09:26,621
[ Man breathing heavily ]

77
00:09:26,732 --> 00:09:29,166
D-daddy, is that you?

78
00:09:30,303 --> 00:09:32,567
Daddy misses you, baby.

79
00:09:36,909 --> 00:09:38,604
Daddy...

80
00:09:38,711 --> 00:09:40,645
Are you better now?

81
00:09:40,746 --> 00:09:43,214
Yes. I am.

82
00:09:43,316 --> 00:09:45,784
Please come home.

83
00:09:45,885 --> 00:09:49,844
Just tell your mother
to bring you all home.

84
00:09:49,956 --> 00:09:52,481
Please!

85
00:09:57,129 --> 00:09:59,757
Did you get rid of it?

86
00:10:01,467 --> 00:10:03,560
Yes.

87
00:10:04,570 --> 00:10:07,505
So there'll be no more crazy talk?

88
00:10:07,607 --> 00:10:09,302
Come home.

89
00:10:09,408 --> 00:10:11,376
Clarence!

90
00:10:12,745 --> 00:10:15,441
Come home, Jean.

91
00:10:17,350 --> 00:10:19,545
I want to, baby.

92
00:10:19,652 --> 00:10:20,880
I miss you, but --

93
00:10:20,987 --> 00:10:22,079
[ Receiver clicks, dial tone ]

94
00:10:25,191 --> 00:10:28,183
[ Bell tolling ]

95
00:10:39,271 --> 00:10:42,570
♪ Had no warning ♪

96
00:10:42,675 --> 00:10:46,941
♪ Give me just a little more time ♪

97
00:10:47,046 --> 00:10:48,980
♪ I know I hit
the fuckin' rock bottom ♪

98
00:10:49,081 --> 00:10:50,776
[ Thumping ]

99
00:10:50,883 --> 00:10:54,114
♪ About a week
from the hurt and the pain ♪

100
00:10:54,220 --> 00:10:56,154
♪ That you must admit ♪

101
00:10:56,255 --> 00:10:57,950
♪ Rock bottom ♪

102
00:10:58,057 --> 00:10:59,888
[ Thumping continues ]

103
00:11:02,194 --> 00:11:05,095
♪ About a week from now ♪

104
00:11:08,567 --> 00:11:09,966
[ Books hit floor ]

105
00:11:10,069 --> 00:11:11,536
Geez, Cari!
Don't you knock?!

106
00:11:11,637 --> 00:11:13,502
Sorry.

107
00:11:13,939 --> 00:11:15,099
Damn it.

108
00:11:15,207 --> 00:11:16,640
[ Music shuts off ]

109
00:11:16,742 --> 00:11:18,437
You said you were studying
at the library today.

110
00:11:18,544 --> 00:11:20,671
I was, but there were
too many people there,

111
00:11:20,780 --> 00:11:22,008
and I just didn't feel like it.

112
00:11:22,114 --> 00:11:23,547
And?

113
00:11:23,649 --> 00:11:26,345
And, well, when the hell am I
supposed to have my time, Cari?

114
00:11:26,452 --> 00:11:28,647
You're here
every fucking minute, studying.

115
00:11:28,754 --> 00:11:30,949
You never go out.

116
00:11:31,057 --> 00:11:33,525
You never go home.

117
00:11:33,626 --> 00:11:35,856
I get no time to myself.

118
00:11:35,961 --> 00:11:38,794
[ Cellphone ringing ]

119
00:11:42,601 --> 00:11:44,535
You gonna answer that?

120
00:11:44,637 --> 00:11:45,831
[ Ringing continues ]

121
00:11:45,938 --> 00:11:47,496
Oh, they'll call back.

122
00:11:47,673 --> 00:11:51,131
It must be her parents.
Again.

123
00:11:52,344 --> 00:11:54,278
Well, lookee here.
What did I tell you?

124
00:11:54,380 --> 00:11:56,814
-Good old M and D calling again.
-Give me that.

125
00:11:56,916 --> 00:11:58,577
What, are you afraid
I'm gonna answer it?

126
00:11:58,751 --> 00:12:01,345
You have no right.

127
00:12:02,521 --> 00:12:03,988
They'll just call back.

128
00:12:06,425 --> 00:12:09,883
And call and call.

129
00:12:09,995 --> 00:12:13,931
Just like they keep sending you
these letters you never open.

130
00:12:16,135 --> 00:12:18,763
Come on.
Let's go to your place.

131
00:12:22,575 --> 00:12:25,009
Do me a favor, Cari,
and answer your phone.

132
00:12:25,111 --> 00:12:28,547
Better yet, just go home.

133
00:12:42,628 --> 00:12:45,222
MAN: Philosopher and poet
George Santayana

134
00:12:45,331 --> 00:12:49,563
was quoted as saying that
those who fail to learn from history

135
00:12:49,668 --> 00:12:52,136
are doomed to repeat it.

136
00:12:52,238 --> 00:12:54,968
These words imply
that society is destined

137
00:12:55,074 --> 00:12:57,804
to travel down
the same self-destructive road

138
00:12:57,910 --> 00:13:01,607
until it is willing to accept
the wrongs of its past.

139
00:13:01,714 --> 00:13:04,410
And quite often,
this burden of acceptance

140
00:13:04,517 --> 00:13:07,213
gets passed down to our children.

141
00:13:07,319 --> 00:13:09,787
It's the children who pay the price
for our indiscretions.

142
00:13:09,889 --> 00:13:11,584
[ Dog barking ]

143
00:13:11,690 --> 00:13:13,885
[ Scoffs ]

144
00:13:13,993 --> 00:13:16,962
...the creation
of the atomic bomb...

145
00:13:17,062 --> 00:13:17,960
[ Smack ]

146
00:13:18,063 --> 00:13:20,054
[ inhales sharply ]
Ow!

147
00:13:20,166 --> 00:13:21,599
...enough is enough.

148
00:13:21,734 --> 00:13:24,931
Otherwise, the vicious cycle
will continue.

149
00:13:25,037 --> 00:13:28,632
And tragically, we,
the adults of this generation...

150
00:13:28,741 --> 00:13:31,141
[ Voice trails off ]

151
00:13:34,713 --> 00:13:36,772
...the price tag will be human life.

152
00:13:36,882 --> 00:13:38,474
[ Panting ]

153
00:13:38,584 --> 00:13:42,281
...society, in all its complacency,
is willing to accept the notion

154
00:13:42,388 --> 00:13:45,687
that its children
are tomorrow's martyrs.

155
00:13:51,864 --> 00:13:52,558
[ Crack ]

156
00:13:52,665 --> 00:13:54,599
[ Gasps ]

157
00:14:07,847 --> 00:14:09,781
[ Crackling ]

158
00:14:18,324 --> 00:14:20,588
[ Panting ]

159
00:14:25,664 --> 00:14:27,859
[ Chair slides ]

160
00:14:50,723 --> 00:14:52,816
[ Crackling ]

161
00:15:17,116 --> 00:15:18,583
[ Water running ]

162
00:15:24,823 --> 00:15:26,848
Ohh.

163
00:15:26,959 --> 00:15:29,189
[ Sobbing ]

164
00:15:44,843 --> 00:15:46,902
[ Thunder rumbles ]

165
00:16:16,008 --> 00:16:17,100
MAN: Campus operator.

166
00:16:17,209 --> 00:16:18,733
Hi, this is Cari Lumis.

167
00:16:18,844 --> 00:16:22,075
Could you give me the number
to the campus clinic, please?

168
00:16:22,181 --> 00:16:24,115
I have an emergency.

169
00:16:24,216 --> 00:16:26,446
Please hold.

170
00:16:28,554 --> 00:16:30,613
[ Cellphone ringing ]

171
00:16:50,075 --> 00:16:50,973
Mom?

172
00:16:51,076 --> 00:16:52,737
KARL: No, honey.
This is your father.

173
00:16:52,845 --> 00:16:55,678
Aw, Dad.
Dad, there's something wrong.

174
00:16:55,781 --> 00:16:56,873
Cari, you're sick.

175
00:16:56,982 --> 00:16:59,416
No, Dad.
Dad, it's more than that.

176
00:16:59,518 --> 00:17:00,849
My skin, it --

177
00:17:00,953 --> 00:17:04,286
It's drying up,
and you have unexplained sores.

178
00:17:04,390 --> 00:17:06,585
How did you know?

179
00:17:06,692 --> 00:17:08,660
Sweetie, you have --

180
00:17:08,761 --> 00:17:12,026
You have a family-related illness.

181
00:17:12,131 --> 00:17:13,496
It's hereditary.

182
00:17:13,599 --> 00:17:15,794
Dad, you never said anything
about this.

183
00:17:15,901 --> 00:17:19,393
Dad, it's bad.
I think I need a doctor.

184
00:17:19,505 --> 00:17:21,700
We have the remedy here.

185
00:17:21,807 --> 00:17:24,298
So you must come home, and
you must come home immediately.

186
00:17:24,410 --> 00:17:28,403
Okay. Okay. It hurts.

187
00:17:28,514 --> 00:17:31,449
Cari, we have the cure.

188
00:17:31,550 --> 00:17:35,714
You just come home now.
But make it quick.

189
00:17:59,278 --> 00:18:00,074
[ Sighs ]

190
00:18:00,179 --> 00:18:02,647
It's gonna be all right, Maggie.

191
00:18:03,549 --> 00:18:06,245
Gonna be all right.

192
00:18:22,468 --> 00:18:23,765
MAGGIE: Daniel...

193
00:18:24,536 --> 00:18:26,265
I'm thirsty.

194
00:18:26,839 --> 00:18:28,500
You can have my rations.

195
00:18:29,141 --> 00:18:32,599
No. I need water.

196
00:18:32,711 --> 00:18:33,905
There's little left.

197
00:18:34,012 --> 00:18:35,138
[ Sighs ]

198
00:18:35,781 --> 00:18:38,215
I'll check with Pa.

199
00:18:41,153 --> 00:18:43,849
Pa, can Maggie have
my water rations?

200
00:18:43,956 --> 00:18:45,924
No.

201
00:18:46,024 --> 00:18:47,013
Pa...

202
00:18:47,126 --> 00:18:48,991
that boy in the field --

203
00:18:49,094 --> 00:18:51,824
he was Ben Wheeler's son, Simon.

204
00:18:51,997 --> 00:18:53,362
[ inhales deeply ]

205
00:18:53,465 --> 00:18:55,626
Yeah.

206
00:18:55,734 --> 00:18:57,964
That boy was crazy.

207
00:18:58,070 --> 00:19:01,369
Lack of food and water, no doubt.

208
00:19:02,141 --> 00:19:03,972
What happened to him, Pa?

209
00:19:05,210 --> 00:19:07,542
[ Thunder rumbles ]

210
00:19:19,324 --> 00:19:21,349
My God.

211
00:19:29,535 --> 00:19:31,503
Ha!

212
00:19:31,603 --> 00:19:32,763
[ Chuckles ]

213
00:19:32,871 --> 00:19:36,864
Pa, it looks like our prayers
came through.

214
00:19:36,975 --> 00:19:38,135
Ha.

215
00:19:38,243 --> 00:19:40,871
Looks like it.

216
00:20:01,033 --> 00:20:03,126
[ Thunder crashes ]

217
00:20:21,520 --> 00:20:23,181
[ Sighs ]

218
00:20:23,288 --> 00:20:25,119
Can this day get any worse?

219
00:20:29,194 --> 00:20:31,424
Well, well, well.
If it isn't Cari Lumis.

220
00:20:31,530 --> 00:20:33,088
What's going on, Sheriff?

221
00:20:33,198 --> 00:20:36,793
Well, we've got some flooding.
We're re-routing traffic.

222
00:20:37,369 --> 00:20:38,563
Oh, okay.

223
00:20:38,670 --> 00:20:40,729
Well, does that mean
I have to turn around, then?

224
00:20:40,839 --> 00:20:42,670
No.

225
00:20:42,774 --> 00:20:45,868
We don't turn away our own kind.

226
00:20:48,146 --> 00:20:49,875
Okay, well, I better get going.

227
00:20:49,982 --> 00:20:52,473
My parents are probably
waiting for me.

228
00:20:52,584 --> 00:20:56,111
Well, you let me move those first.

229
00:20:58,657 --> 00:21:01,057
[ Power window hums ]

230
00:21:08,634 --> 00:21:10,602
[ Thunder rumbles ]

231
00:22:05,891 --> 00:22:07,882
[ Thunder crashes ]

232
00:22:33,151 --> 00:22:35,142
[ insects buzzing ]

233
00:22:46,031 --> 00:22:47,999
[ Crow caws ]

234
00:23:34,780 --> 00:23:36,372
[ Truck door closes ]

235
00:24:02,441 --> 00:24:04,636
[ Crow cawing ]

236
00:24:04,743 --> 00:24:06,574
[ Door opens ]

237
00:24:08,780 --> 00:24:10,748
[ Gasps softly ]

238
00:24:12,451 --> 00:24:15,545
Welcome home, everybody.

239
00:24:15,720 --> 00:24:17,984
Daddy!

240
00:24:23,962 --> 00:24:26,897
Let's all get in out of the heat.

241
00:24:26,998 --> 00:24:28,431
CLARENCE: Come on.

242
00:24:29,367 --> 00:24:31,631
Come on, baby. It's still daddy.

243
00:24:37,108 --> 00:24:38,598
[ Rain falling ]

244
00:24:53,124 --> 00:24:55,251
[ Cari coughing ]

245
00:25:02,601 --> 00:25:04,535
ELEANOR: Drink this.

246
00:25:04,636 --> 00:25:06,263
What is it?

247
00:25:06,371 --> 00:25:07,360
KARL: Just --

248
00:25:08,473 --> 00:25:09,667
Just drink it, dear.

249
00:25:09,774 --> 00:25:11,799
Just drink it.

250
00:25:24,623 --> 00:25:26,420
Ahh.

251
00:25:27,158 --> 00:25:29,058
I can breathe! What was that?

252
00:25:29,728 --> 00:25:31,923
It's a remedy.

253
00:25:32,030 --> 00:25:35,090
Now take the bandages off.

254
00:25:50,215 --> 00:25:51,910
Ohh.

255
00:25:52,017 --> 00:25:53,484
Ohh!

256
00:26:02,761 --> 00:26:05,059
It's working.

257
00:26:06,731 --> 00:26:08,096
I need more.

258
00:26:08,233 --> 00:26:10,360
[ Thumping ]

259
00:26:14,306 --> 00:26:16,672
I'll give you more.

260
00:26:17,842 --> 00:26:22,040
But you got to do exactly
what I say, without question.

261
00:26:22,147 --> 00:26:23,637
-Do you understand?
-Yes.

262
00:26:23,748 --> 00:26:25,409
-You understand?
-Yes!

263
00:26:25,517 --> 00:26:28,008
Now, that's a promise.

264
00:26:29,120 --> 00:26:31,816
'Cause if you don't...

265
00:26:31,923 --> 00:26:34,323
I can't help you.

266
00:26:49,341 --> 00:26:51,036
Listen to me.

267
00:26:51,142 --> 00:26:53,770
You listen to me.

268
00:26:54,980 --> 00:26:59,212
Your illness is hereditary.

269
00:26:59,317 --> 00:27:01,785
You could say it's a...

270
00:27:01,886 --> 00:27:04,616
it's a curse.

271
00:27:04,723 --> 00:27:08,682
It occurs when you reach adulthood...

272
00:27:08,793 --> 00:27:10,192
and it can kill you.

273
00:27:10,295 --> 00:27:12,160
-[ Gasps ]
-Shh. Shh. Shh. Shh.

274
00:27:12,263 --> 00:27:13,787
But there is a cure.

275
00:27:27,245 --> 00:27:28,610
[ Groans ]

276
00:27:28,713 --> 00:27:31,682
Shh. Shh.

277
00:27:33,985 --> 00:27:35,577
No, no, no.

278
00:27:35,687 --> 00:27:37,052
Now...

279
00:27:37,155 --> 00:27:38,986
I want you...

280
00:27:39,090 --> 00:27:44,187
I want you to let go of your pain...

281
00:27:46,131 --> 00:27:50,568
...and walk into the healing rain.

282
00:30:20,852 --> 00:30:22,843
[ Fire crackling ]

283
00:30:28,927 --> 00:30:31,691
MAGGIE: Daniel, you awake?

284
00:30:31,796 --> 00:30:33,161
Yeah.

285
00:30:33,264 --> 00:30:36,961
I'm thirsty. You think you can
just sneak a little water?

286
00:30:37,068 --> 00:30:40,094
Pa said we could have
some rations in the morning.

287
00:30:40,205 --> 00:30:43,106
I can't sleep. Please.

288
00:30:43,208 --> 00:30:45,369
All right.

289
00:30:57,722 --> 00:30:59,656
What's the matter?

290
00:31:00,959 --> 00:31:02,824
Thinking about what the boy said?

291
00:31:03,494 --> 00:31:04,654
Yeah.

292
00:31:04,762 --> 00:31:06,059
Well, don't be afraid.

293
00:31:06,164 --> 00:31:08,394
All he saw was the hat, right?

294
00:31:08,499 --> 00:31:11,161
Yeah, but even monsters
can wear hats.

295
00:31:12,003 --> 00:31:14,233
There's no such thing as monsters.

296
00:31:15,406 --> 00:31:17,203
[ Sighs ]

297
00:31:33,124 --> 00:31:35,092
[ Thumping ]

298
00:31:49,674 --> 00:31:52,268
[ Footsteps approach ]

299
00:32:00,084 --> 00:32:01,312
[ Grunts ]

300
00:32:09,427 --> 00:32:10,951
Getting water, huh?

301
00:32:11,062 --> 00:32:13,394
It's for Maggie.

302
00:32:18,603 --> 00:32:20,400
[ Water splashes ]

303
00:32:22,173 --> 00:32:24,539
Go on in the house.

304
00:32:27,412 --> 00:32:28,709
What's going on?

305
00:32:29,847 --> 00:32:31,280
Heh, heh, heh, heh.

306
00:32:31,382 --> 00:32:32,713
Rain.

307
00:32:32,817 --> 00:32:35,479
The shaman delivered
on his promise.

308
00:32:35,586 --> 00:32:37,986
Skeptics are worried.

309
00:32:38,089 --> 00:32:39,954
We need to choose another one.

310
00:32:40,124 --> 00:32:44,754
Now. Before they change
their minds.

311
00:32:44,929 --> 00:32:47,796
Maybe they're right
to be worried, Horace.

312
00:32:49,167 --> 00:32:51,897
We already had
this conversation, Clive.

313
00:32:52,003 --> 00:32:53,402
You turning yellow on us?

314
00:32:54,739 --> 00:32:56,764
The shaman promised us rain.

315
00:32:56,908 --> 00:32:59,706
And we need this.

316
00:32:59,811 --> 00:33:01,711
And what's next?

317
00:33:01,813 --> 00:33:03,678
What happens next here, Horace?

318
00:33:03,848 --> 00:33:06,112
We'll worry about that later.

319
00:33:06,217 --> 00:33:08,583
Right now we need
to see this through,

320
00:33:08,686 --> 00:33:12,247
or we're all dead
and there is no next year.

321
00:33:14,192 --> 00:33:15,557
Come on, Clive!

322
00:33:15,727 --> 00:33:17,194
What's it gonna take?

323
00:33:17,295 --> 00:33:19,627
All the crops are gone,
our livestock.

324
00:33:20,331 --> 00:33:22,458
We lost, what, 30 to the drought?

325
00:33:22,633 --> 00:33:24,931
3 1 .

326
00:33:25,036 --> 00:33:25,798
Yeah.

327
00:33:25,937 --> 00:33:28,098
Right. Whatever.

328
00:33:28,206 --> 00:33:30,868
It's gonna be 33.

329
00:33:30,975 --> 00:33:32,636
Two more, Clive...

330
00:33:32,744 --> 00:33:34,109
and we all live.

331
00:33:34,212 --> 00:33:36,077
[ Groans ]

332
00:33:41,285 --> 00:33:43,344
We're all in this equal.

333
00:33:43,454 --> 00:33:45,718
Ain't that right, Ben?

334
00:33:46,958 --> 00:33:48,687
All right!

335
00:33:49,394 --> 00:33:51,862
You made your point.

336
00:33:54,165 --> 00:33:56,156
I'll go.

337
00:33:56,334 --> 00:33:58,802
Good man, Clive.

338
00:33:59,904 --> 00:34:02,270
Good man.

339
00:34:08,613 --> 00:34:09,637
Where you going?

340
00:34:09,747 --> 00:34:12,079
Into town.

341
00:34:12,183 --> 00:34:14,674
I'll be back before long.

342
00:34:14,786 --> 00:34:17,721
You watch over your sister.

343
00:34:19,957 --> 00:34:21,481
[ Door opens ]

344
00:34:22,560 --> 00:34:23,584
[ Door closes ]

345
00:34:25,530 --> 00:34:27,998
But how can rainwater be a cure?

346
00:34:28,099 --> 00:34:30,124
It can't be that simple, can it?

347
00:34:30,301 --> 00:34:32,633
Yes, it can.

348
00:34:32,737 --> 00:34:37,674
From now on you have to bathe
in the vernal rain.

349
00:34:39,644 --> 00:34:41,635
The vernal rain?

350
00:34:41,813 --> 00:34:44,646
Yes, the vernal rain. It's a...

351
00:34:45,917 --> 00:34:47,976
It's a rain that comes once a year.

352
00:34:48,086 --> 00:34:50,611
It has special properties.

353
00:34:50,721 --> 00:34:53,815
You have to shower in it...

354
00:34:53,925 --> 00:34:58,555
or your affliction will return...

355
00:34:59,297 --> 00:35:01,527
and you'll die.

356
00:35:02,400 --> 00:35:06,496
Well, what about
Kyle, Max, and Jack?

357
00:35:07,772 --> 00:35:10,605
Your brothers...

358
00:35:15,480 --> 00:35:17,948
Your brothers...

359
00:35:21,652 --> 00:35:23,517
Look...

360
00:35:23,621 --> 00:35:25,919
You...

361
00:35:26,023 --> 00:35:28,150
me, your mother --

362
00:35:29,760 --> 00:35:33,321
we were all born with this curse.

363
00:35:33,898 --> 00:35:34,626
Mom?

364
00:35:39,604 --> 00:35:42,573
Well, what if it doesn't rain
next time? Then, what?

365
00:35:44,342 --> 00:35:47,368
We have a way of ensuring...

366
00:35:49,013 --> 00:35:50,002
that it will rain.

367
00:35:50,181 --> 00:35:53,241
Well, you can't just make it rain.

368
00:35:55,486 --> 00:35:57,716
Yes, we can.

369
00:35:58,656 --> 00:36:02,023
I think it's time you come with me.
I've got to show you something.

370
00:36:05,062 --> 00:36:08,054
[ Man on radio speaking indistinctly ]

371
00:36:10,535 --> 00:36:13,663
[ Jean coughing ]

372
00:36:45,069 --> 00:36:47,003
[ Clarence groans ]

373
00:37:06,123 --> 00:37:08,250
[ Water splashing ]

374
00:37:11,128 --> 00:37:13,096
[ Jean coughing ]

375
00:37:17,635 --> 00:37:19,068
JEAN: Mandy...

376
00:37:19,237 --> 00:37:22,468
your dinner's getting cold.

377
00:37:23,140 --> 00:37:24,607
Let's all say grace, please.

378
00:37:28,279 --> 00:37:31,339
Dear Lord, we thank You
that we can all be together

379
00:37:31,449 --> 00:37:34,111
around this table again.

380
00:37:37,688 --> 00:37:39,519
Thank You for...

381
00:37:41,025 --> 00:37:43,118
letting us remember...

382
00:37:43,227 --> 00:37:44,717
that as long as we're together,

383
00:37:44,829 --> 00:37:48,128
we can get through
all your trials and tribulations.

384
00:37:48,299 --> 00:37:49,391
Amen.

385
00:37:49,500 --> 00:37:51,900
[ Coughs ]

386
00:37:52,937 --> 00:37:55,428
CLARENCE: Hope you like it.

387
00:37:57,275 --> 00:37:59,505
[ Coughing ]

388
00:38:12,423 --> 00:38:16,052
[ Coughing ]
Clarence, I don't feel so good.

389
00:39:10,614 --> 00:39:12,241
MAGGIE: Where are you going?

390
00:39:12,416 --> 00:39:14,350
Going to get Pa from town.

391
00:39:14,452 --> 00:39:16,420
He said to wait here.

392
00:39:16,587 --> 00:39:19,055
Something's wrong.
He's been gone too long.

393
00:39:19,223 --> 00:39:21,384
You think he's in trouble?

394
00:39:21,559 --> 00:39:23,720
I don't know. Maybe.

395
00:39:23,828 --> 00:39:27,889
It didn't look like he wanted
to go with them.

396
00:39:28,799 --> 00:39:32,235
Daniel, why is this happening to us?

397
00:39:32,870 --> 00:39:35,065
I'm afraid, Daniel.
Don't leave me.

398
00:39:35,172 --> 00:39:36,696
I don't want to be alone.

399
00:39:36,874 --> 00:39:39,104
Listen, the town's not that far away.

400
00:39:39,210 --> 00:39:42,543
I can make it in an hour
and be back before too long.

401
00:39:42,646 --> 00:39:45,012
I'll be careful.

402
00:39:46,016 --> 00:39:48,007
I'm scared to be here by myself.

403
00:39:48,686 --> 00:39:52,622
Don't be. There's no such thing
as monsters, remember?

404
00:40:03,567 --> 00:40:06,161
Tell you what -- why don't you
bar the door behind me,

405
00:40:06,270 --> 00:40:08,261
and I'll knock like this...

406
00:40:11,308 --> 00:40:13,606
...to let me back in, okay?

407
00:40:13,711 --> 00:40:15,679
Now, get back to bed.

408
00:40:15,780 --> 00:40:17,805
People can be monsters, too,
Daniel.

409
00:40:23,954 --> 00:40:26,320
[ Door opens ]

410
00:40:31,929 --> 00:40:34,864
[ Thunder rumbles, rain falling ]

411
00:40:42,873 --> 00:40:45,569
Now, listen to me, Cari.

412
00:40:47,077 --> 00:40:49,375
I want you to listen to me.

413
00:40:50,381 --> 00:40:53,179
I need you to do something.

414
00:40:53,284 --> 00:40:56,082
It's gonna be hard at first,

415
00:40:56,187 --> 00:40:59,679
but I want you
to understand that it's...

416
00:40:59,790 --> 00:41:01,883
it's for the survival of this family.

417
00:41:01,992 --> 00:41:04,552
Do you understand?

418
00:41:04,662 --> 00:41:06,323
That's a promise?

419
00:41:06,430 --> 00:41:09,058
Yes, Daddy.

420
00:41:09,166 --> 00:41:11,225
Okay.

421
00:41:30,054 --> 00:41:30,952
Kyle!

422
00:41:32,590 --> 00:41:34,114
Why is he tied up?!

423
00:41:34,291 --> 00:41:35,485
So he doesn't get away.

424
00:41:35,593 --> 00:41:38,153
"Get away"?
He needs a doctor.

425
00:41:38,262 --> 00:41:40,230
Cari. Cari.

426
00:41:41,732 --> 00:41:43,893
Listen to me.

427
00:41:45,469 --> 00:41:49,132
We can talk about this later.
We can discuss it later.

428
00:41:49,240 --> 00:41:53,438
What I need you to do --
listen very carefully now --

429
00:41:53,544 --> 00:41:56,012
is I need you to take your hands...

430
00:41:56,113 --> 00:41:58,980
take your hands...

431
00:41:59,083 --> 00:42:02,211
place them on his chest.

432
00:42:02,786 --> 00:42:08,656
And submerge him
until his lungs fill with water.

433
00:42:09,760 --> 00:42:10,749
No!

434
00:42:10,861 --> 00:42:11,850
Cari!

435
00:42:11,962 --> 00:42:13,623
Look at this!

436
00:42:14,832 --> 00:42:16,561
Look at it!

437
00:42:17,468 --> 00:42:19,333
It's not gonna get any better.

438
00:42:19,937 --> 00:42:21,131
You understand?

439
00:42:21,238 --> 00:42:22,728
Stop! You're insane!

440
00:42:22,840 --> 00:42:24,034
Cari!

441
00:42:24,575 --> 00:42:26,543
Listen to me.

442
00:42:26,644 --> 00:42:29,204
If you don't do this...

443
00:42:29,313 --> 00:42:33,909
me, you, your mother --
all of us --

444
00:42:34,018 --> 00:42:37,749
we're gonna die
a horrific and agonizing death.

445
00:42:37,922 --> 00:42:39,219
-Stop!
-Cari!

446
00:42:39,323 --> 00:42:41,553
-Stop! You're hurting me!
-Cari!

447
00:42:41,659 --> 00:42:43,092
You don't understand.

448
00:42:44,595 --> 00:42:46,495
In order to bring the rain...

449
00:42:46,597 --> 00:42:48,497
[ Thunder crashes ]

450
00:42:48,599 --> 00:42:51,625
...we as a family
must make a sacrifice.

451
00:42:51,735 --> 00:42:53,828
We must make a sacrifice.

452
00:42:55,606 --> 00:42:58,632
It's been going on
for over a generation.

453
00:43:00,678 --> 00:43:02,009
I'm gonna call the sheriff.

454
00:43:02,112 --> 00:43:04,171
Doesn't matter.

455
00:43:04,281 --> 00:43:06,249
He knows.

456
00:43:06,350 --> 00:43:08,648
He already knows.

457
00:43:08,752 --> 00:43:12,552
The whole community knows.

458
00:43:14,825 --> 00:43:18,056
We all suffer
from the same curse, Cari.

459
00:43:18,162 --> 00:43:22,030
Our lives... our health...
our crops...

460
00:43:22,132 --> 00:43:23,429
everything.

461
00:43:23,534 --> 00:43:25,331
[ Thunder rumbles ]

462
00:43:25,436 --> 00:43:28,667
And the only way to fix it

463
00:43:28,772 --> 00:43:31,104
is that you have to sacrifice
your brother Kyle.

464
00:43:33,877 --> 00:43:35,742
This is a hoax.

465
00:43:35,846 --> 00:43:38,178
Please stop. Stop it now.

466
00:43:38,282 --> 00:43:39,681
You're lying.

467
00:43:39,850 --> 00:43:44,549
Stop being so dramatic
and do as you're told!

468
00:43:44,655 --> 00:43:46,885
You made a promise.
Now keep it!

469
00:43:46,991 --> 00:43:48,686
How do you think...

470
00:43:48,792 --> 00:43:53,286
Perseverance has prospered
all these years?

471
00:43:53,397 --> 00:43:54,557
Have you looked around?

472
00:43:54,665 --> 00:43:57,498
Have you looked
at all the towns around you?

473
00:43:57,601 --> 00:44:01,037
Huh? They're all dried up.

474
00:44:01,138 --> 00:44:02,969
Why?

475
00:44:03,073 --> 00:44:05,769
Because we made a promise.

476
00:44:05,876 --> 00:44:10,313
And that promise has to be fulfilled.

477
00:44:10,414 --> 00:44:12,905
Now, I want you...

478
00:44:13,017 --> 00:44:15,212
to make it rain.

479
00:44:15,919 --> 00:44:18,717
You make it rain.

480
00:44:18,822 --> 00:44:20,756
Do you hear me?

481
00:44:22,559 --> 00:44:24,857
But it's already raining.

482
00:44:28,866 --> 00:44:31,391
Where's Max?

483
00:44:32,536 --> 00:44:33,935
Where's Jack?

484
00:44:34,038 --> 00:44:36,006
[ Thunder rumbles ]

485
00:44:37,007 --> 00:44:38,838
[ Gasps ]

486
00:44:40,077 --> 00:44:43,604
Oh, God. No. No.

487
00:44:46,850 --> 00:44:49,045
No.

488
00:45:23,053 --> 00:45:25,487
[ Thunder crashes ]

489
00:45:25,589 --> 00:45:27,079
You'll learn, Cari.

490
00:45:27,991 --> 00:45:30,653
You'll learn
like all of us had to learn --

491
00:45:30,761 --> 00:45:32,854
the whole town...

492
00:45:33,630 --> 00:45:38,124
that one day,
when you have your children,

493
00:45:38,235 --> 00:45:41,102
your turn will come.

494
00:45:41,271 --> 00:45:45,139
I just pray that you'll have
the determination

495
00:45:45,242 --> 00:45:49,975
to do exactly
what my father did with me...

496
00:45:51,381 --> 00:45:54,612
...and that I have to do
with you now.

497
00:45:54,718 --> 00:45:57,243
May you have the strength...

498
00:45:58,122 --> 00:46:00,716
to pull the trigger.

499
00:46:39,363 --> 00:46:41,490
[ Coin falls ]

500
00:47:27,411 --> 00:47:29,242
No. No!

501
00:47:29,346 --> 00:47:31,439
It wasn't supposed to go like that!

502
00:47:31,548 --> 00:47:33,778
And what way was that, Clive?!

503
00:47:33,884 --> 00:47:36,011
BOY: The selection has been made.

504
00:47:36,186 --> 00:47:39,451
The shaman now demands
a sacrifice.

505
00:47:39,556 --> 00:47:43,617
If you go back on your word,
he will curse your land and people.

506
00:47:47,531 --> 00:47:49,089
Stop it, Ben.

507
00:47:49,266 --> 00:47:50,255
Stop it!

508
00:47:50,367 --> 00:47:51,561
BEN: No more children!

509
00:47:51,668 --> 00:47:52,930
Let it go, Ben!

510
00:47:53,036 --> 00:47:55,470
Ben. Ben.

511
00:47:55,572 --> 00:47:57,506
We got rain.

512
00:47:57,674 --> 00:47:59,938
There's no going back now.

513
00:48:01,845 --> 00:48:04,871
How can you just let
your babies go?!

514
00:48:04,982 --> 00:48:06,609
Why the children?!

515
00:48:06,783 --> 00:48:09,718
Why don't you take one of us?!

516
00:48:09,887 --> 00:48:11,946
The shaman was a father.

517
00:48:12,055 --> 00:48:15,422
The white man like you
killed his children.

518
00:48:15,525 --> 00:48:17,891
His heart is now dark.

519
00:48:17,995 --> 00:48:21,123
The same darkness is now on you.

520
00:48:22,966 --> 00:48:25,457
[ Clacking ]

521
00:48:46,723 --> 00:48:48,520
Mr. Wheeler.

522
00:48:48,625 --> 00:48:50,616
I saw Simon this morning.

523
00:48:51,728 --> 00:48:52,717
My boy?

524
00:48:52,930 --> 00:48:55,660
Outside the forest, by our property.

525
00:48:55,766 --> 00:48:57,734
He came running out of the woods.

526
00:48:57,901 --> 00:48:59,129
And?

527
00:48:59,236 --> 00:49:02,205
He was hurt real bad, screaming
that he was being chased.

528
00:49:04,041 --> 00:49:05,269
Where is he now?

529
00:49:05,442 --> 00:49:07,501
I don't know, Mr. Wheeler.

530
00:49:07,611 --> 00:49:09,476
My pa...

531
00:49:09,579 --> 00:49:12,673
my pa took him
back into the woods.

532
00:49:12,849 --> 00:49:14,510
Listen to me, Daniel Jonis.

533
00:49:14,685 --> 00:49:17,916
Don't go home.
Stay away till dawn.

534
00:49:18,021 --> 00:49:19,010
Why?

535
00:49:19,189 --> 00:49:23,956
So you don't end up like my boy.

536
00:49:38,976 --> 00:49:41,069
[ Breathing heavily ]

537
00:49:54,958 --> 00:49:56,118
[ Gasps ]

538
00:49:56,226 --> 00:49:57,659
It's okay. It's okay.

539
00:49:57,828 --> 00:50:00,558
It's okay. It's okay.

540
00:50:00,664 --> 00:50:02,359
It's cool.

541
00:50:02,466 --> 00:50:03,262
[ Sighs ]

542
00:50:03,367 --> 00:50:04,265
Yeah.

543
00:50:17,881 --> 00:50:19,212
What's that?

544
00:50:20,650 --> 00:50:23,244
[ Gasping ]

545
00:50:34,831 --> 00:50:37,857
You said you got rid of it!
You promised, Clarence!

546
00:50:37,968 --> 00:50:41,028
Yes, I did, Jean. I promised.

547
00:50:41,138 --> 00:50:43,368
I promised the whole town...

548
00:50:43,473 --> 00:50:47,204
that I would put an end
to this drought, which I started...

549
00:50:48,145 --> 00:50:51,012
that I'd put an end
to this suffering.

550
00:50:51,948 --> 00:50:54,917
And I intend on keeping
that promise.

551
00:50:55,085 --> 00:50:57,144
[ Gasping ]

552
00:50:59,856 --> 00:51:01,949
[ Panting ]

553
00:51:14,304 --> 00:51:17,501
[ Gasping ]

554
00:51:35,292 --> 00:51:40,594
I'm gonna let it fuckin' kill you, Cari,
if you don't do exactly what I say.

555
00:51:40,764 --> 00:51:44,700
Please. Please take it
away from me. I can't breathe!

556
00:51:44,801 --> 00:51:48,532
I promise. I promise.

557
00:51:48,638 --> 00:51:51,436
But you have to do
exactly what I say.

558
00:51:51,541 --> 00:51:54,305
Do you understand?

559
00:51:54,411 --> 00:51:56,402
Is that a yes?

560
00:51:56,513 --> 00:51:57,946
Is that a yes?

561
00:52:01,985 --> 00:52:03,475
Promise.

562
00:52:03,653 --> 00:52:05,280
You promise what?

563
00:52:05,455 --> 00:52:07,013
I want you to say it.

564
00:52:07,124 --> 00:52:11,151
I promise to drown Kyle.

565
00:52:19,636 --> 00:52:22,628
l heard a promise, Cari.

566
00:52:54,804 --> 00:52:56,499
Yeah.

567
00:52:57,541 --> 00:52:59,702
Yeah, that's it.

568
00:53:02,012 --> 00:53:04,378
That's it.

569
00:53:12,189 --> 00:53:13,747
[ Thunder crashes ]

570
00:53:21,898 --> 00:53:22,922
Kyle.

571
00:53:24,334 --> 00:53:26,859
-[ Kyle gasping ]
-Kyle!

572
00:53:27,037 --> 00:53:29,062
Enough with you!

573
00:53:29,839 --> 00:53:32,433
I'll deal with you later!

574
00:53:32,609 --> 00:53:35,271
I'll show you how to do it.

575
00:53:37,581 --> 00:53:39,572
I'll show you how to do it.

576
00:53:41,585 --> 00:53:43,712
[ Grunting ]

577
00:53:57,033 --> 00:53:58,660
[ Kyle grunting ]

578
00:53:59,836 --> 00:54:02,669
[ Grunting ]

579
00:54:12,048 --> 00:54:14,312
[ Water splashing ]

580
00:54:16,586 --> 00:54:17,814
KYLE: Stop!

581
00:54:23,927 --> 00:54:26,293
[ Thunder rumbles ]

582
00:54:29,232 --> 00:54:30,392
[ Knock on door ]

583
00:54:36,373 --> 00:54:38,603
[ Rattling ]

584
00:54:38,775 --> 00:54:40,470
[ Grunting ]

585
00:54:40,577 --> 00:54:43,102
Shh. Shh. Shh.

586
00:54:43,513 --> 00:54:45,208
Can you breathe?

587
00:54:51,321 --> 00:54:54,779
They -- they killed Max and Jack.

588
00:54:55,659 --> 00:54:57,251
-I tried to stop 'em.
-Shh.

589
00:54:57,360 --> 00:54:59,328
Don't talk.

590
00:54:59,429 --> 00:55:01,693
We need to get out of here now.

591
00:55:01,798 --> 00:55:03,823
ELEANOR: Cari, open the door.

592
00:55:03,933 --> 00:55:05,958
Through the window.

593
00:55:08,405 --> 00:55:09,702
Karl!

594
00:55:15,945 --> 00:55:18,641
You're putting us all in danger.

595
00:55:18,748 --> 00:55:21,478
Don't listen to her. Go. Now.

596
00:55:30,527 --> 00:55:33,690
Oh, my God.
He wasn't lying.

597
00:55:36,266 --> 00:55:37,665
[ Rain stops ]

598
00:55:37,767 --> 00:55:40,395
[ Groans ]

599
00:55:40,503 --> 00:55:41,663
What's wrong?

600
00:55:41,838 --> 00:55:43,237
[ Crackling ]

601
00:55:43,406 --> 00:55:46,933
Nothing. Go towards
the front of the house.

602
00:56:00,724 --> 00:56:01,884
What about Max and Jack?

603
00:56:01,991 --> 00:56:05,449
It's too late for them, Kyle.
It's not safe here.

604
00:56:18,274 --> 00:56:19,605
No!

605
00:56:20,310 --> 00:56:22,107
[ Crackling ]

606
00:56:22,212 --> 00:56:23,941
[ Groans ]

607
00:56:29,486 --> 00:56:30,783
[ Knife falls ]

608
00:56:30,887 --> 00:56:34,288
Cari!

609
00:57:10,927 --> 00:57:12,588
No one said you could
come down here, Mandy.

610
00:57:14,764 --> 00:57:17,255
Go upstairs
and play with your sister.

611
00:57:17,367 --> 00:57:19,392
Now!

612
00:57:53,369 --> 00:57:56,497
Mama? Oh, God!

613
00:58:17,427 --> 00:58:19,987
[ Both grunting ]

614
00:58:21,164 --> 00:58:23,394
KYLE: Owwww!

615
00:58:32,942 --> 00:58:35,206
[ Thunder crashes ]

616
00:58:51,427 --> 00:58:56,387
Uh, it's only a small cut.
It doesn't hurt much.

617
00:58:56,499 --> 00:58:59,195
Just a little more blood, Kyle.

618
00:58:59,302 --> 00:59:01,736
No! What are you doing?!

619
00:59:01,838 --> 00:59:03,169
-[ Grunts ]
-[ Thunder crashes ]

620
00:59:03,773 --> 00:59:05,764
No! What's wrong with you?

621
00:59:05,942 --> 00:59:07,341
I'm sick.

622
00:59:07,510 --> 00:59:09,478
No!

623
00:59:09,579 --> 00:59:11,206
Not you, too!

624
00:59:11,314 --> 00:59:13,805
You all want to hurt me!

625
00:59:20,290 --> 00:59:22,690
It's the rain.

626
00:59:32,735 --> 00:59:35,203
[ Fire crackling ]

627
00:59:36,139 --> 00:59:39,302
[ indistinct whispering ]

628
00:59:39,409 --> 00:59:42,207
[ Three knocks on door ]

629
00:59:45,848 --> 00:59:48,112
Daniel?

630
00:59:50,520 --> 00:59:53,489
Daniel? Pa?

631
01:00:25,688 --> 01:00:28,350
[ Screams ]

632
01:00:29,425 --> 01:00:31,325
[ indistinct chanting ]

633
01:00:34,731 --> 01:00:36,631
[ Screams ]

634
01:00:37,233 --> 01:00:42,102
The drought has plagued us
for far too long now, Brenda.

635
01:00:42,205 --> 01:00:46,039
Ever since Daddy found the hat...

636
01:00:46,142 --> 01:00:50,169
our farm -- all of the farms,

637
01:00:50,279 --> 01:00:53,976
they're all dead.

638
01:00:54,083 --> 01:00:57,280
Dead because there is no rain!

639
01:00:57,387 --> 01:00:59,753
[ Thunder crashes ]

640
01:01:01,124 --> 01:01:02,489
But that will all change.

641
01:01:03,760 --> 01:01:06,558
Once I give...

642
01:01:06,663 --> 01:01:08,130
Dad, you're sick.

643
01:01:08,231 --> 01:01:10,256
You're sick, and you need help.

644
01:01:10,366 --> 01:01:12,834
You've been sick ever since
you found that thing.

645
01:01:13,603 --> 01:01:15,628
Daddy needs to give first.

646
01:01:15,738 --> 01:01:17,365
-Then all will be well.
-No!

647
01:01:20,443 --> 01:01:22,308
[ Whispering indistinctly ]

648
01:01:22,412 --> 01:01:24,846
[ Coughing ]

649
01:01:31,354 --> 01:01:33,083
[ Door closes ]

650
01:01:35,258 --> 01:01:37,453
[ People coughing ]

651
01:01:49,272 --> 01:01:51,103
Eleanor.

652
01:01:52,275 --> 01:01:53,936
Where are they?

653
01:01:56,646 --> 01:01:59,444
I'm so sorry.

654
01:02:05,021 --> 01:02:07,080
You've failed.

655
01:02:08,424 --> 01:02:11,222
But we have someone
who has never failed.

656
01:02:12,662 --> 01:02:14,129
Mr. Saul.

657
01:02:16,065 --> 01:02:17,828
No.

658
01:02:18,568 --> 01:02:19,592
Not him.

659
01:02:24,574 --> 01:02:26,439
I'll slaughter whatever's left
of my family.

660
01:02:26,542 --> 01:02:28,510
You have nothing to say
about this anymore.

661
01:02:30,813 --> 01:02:34,146
The lottery is in jeopardy
because of you.

662
01:02:37,854 --> 01:02:40,414
You must ensure,
as you have before,

663
01:02:40,523 --> 01:02:43,924
that things are set right.

664
01:02:45,361 --> 01:02:47,989
Hand it over.

665
01:02:50,933 --> 01:02:52,560
You had your chance...

666
01:02:52,735 --> 01:02:54,669
and you failed.

667
01:02:54,771 --> 01:02:58,298
It's all in Mr. Saul's hands now.

668
01:03:03,980 --> 01:03:06,039
ELEANOR: Only the boy.

669
01:03:06,149 --> 01:03:08,743
H-he was the chosen one.

670
01:03:23,232 --> 01:03:25,097
[ Panting ]

671
01:03:26,636 --> 01:03:29,036
Maggie?!

672
01:04:18,221 --> 01:04:20,849
[ Dog panting ]

673
01:04:43,512 --> 01:04:45,639
Kyle?

674
01:04:45,748 --> 01:04:47,943
Kyle?!

675
01:04:50,586 --> 01:04:52,986
[ Dog barking ]

676
01:05:17,313 --> 01:05:19,907
Where are you taking me?

677
01:05:22,018 --> 01:05:23,451
[ Dog whines ]

678
01:05:35,865 --> 01:05:37,628
Kyle!

679
01:05:38,534 --> 01:05:41,469
I am so sorry.

680
01:05:41,570 --> 01:05:42,935
I want to go back home.

681
01:05:43,039 --> 01:05:45,940
I know. I do, too. But we can't.

682
01:05:46,108 --> 01:05:49,305
But Dad's hurt. Maybe we should
go back and help him.

683
01:05:49,412 --> 01:05:52,074
Kyle, Dad tried to hurt us.

684
01:05:52,181 --> 01:05:54,081
Mom did, too.

685
01:05:54,183 --> 01:05:57,675
They murdered Max and Jack.

686
01:05:57,853 --> 01:05:59,980
They have an illness
that made them do this.

687
01:06:00,089 --> 01:06:02,421
They're not themselves.

688
01:06:02,591 --> 01:06:04,650
But can't we get them to a doctor?

689
01:06:05,995 --> 01:06:08,156
Kyle, we can't go back.

690
01:06:08,264 --> 01:06:12,064
We can't call a doctor.
The whole town is in on it.

691
01:06:14,804 --> 01:06:16,135
We're gonna be okay.

692
01:06:16,739 --> 01:06:19,037
What's gonna happen to us?

693
01:06:19,141 --> 01:06:21,268
Listen, I promise you --

694
01:06:21,377 --> 01:06:23,845
from now on,
I will take care of you.

695
01:06:23,946 --> 01:06:25,243
Okay? I promise.

696
01:06:25,348 --> 01:06:27,441
No! You don't care!

697
01:06:27,550 --> 01:06:28,539
What?!

698
01:06:28,718 --> 01:06:31,448
Mom and Dad said
you didn't care about us.

699
01:06:31,554 --> 01:06:32,145
Kyle!

700
01:06:32,254 --> 01:06:34,279
That's why you left
and ran away to college.

701
01:06:34,457 --> 01:06:36,857
Of course I care about you!

702
01:06:36,959 --> 01:06:38,893
All I've ever known
is Perseverance.

703
01:06:38,995 --> 01:06:41,964
I had to go and see
what is out there.

704
01:06:42,064 --> 01:06:45,659
Mom and Dad were always
trying to hold me back.

705
01:06:45,768 --> 01:06:48,362
And now I know why.

706
01:06:49,839 --> 01:06:51,329
We've got to get out of this town.

707
01:06:51,440 --> 01:06:53,203
I mean, maybe we can
go back to my school.

708
01:06:53,309 --> 01:06:56,005
Maybe we can find help there.

709
01:06:56,178 --> 01:06:57,338
What are you looking for?

710
01:06:57,446 --> 01:07:01,143
Keys. Maybe we can drive
this truck out of here.

711
01:07:01,317 --> 01:07:03,683
And what? Just steal it?

712
01:07:03,786 --> 01:07:05,686
I don't know.
That house is abandoned.

713
01:07:05,788 --> 01:07:08,382
Nobody will notice.

714
01:07:10,226 --> 01:07:13,024
[ Engine sputtering ]

715
01:07:14,530 --> 01:07:18,261
Oh, damn! It's on empty!

716
01:07:19,001 --> 01:07:22,402
Maybe there's some fuel
in the barn.

717
01:08:28,237 --> 01:08:30,228
Kyle, what are you doing?

718
01:08:30,339 --> 01:08:33,604
We've got to find fuel.
We don't have time for that.

719
01:08:35,244 --> 01:08:36,506
But I'm starving.

720
01:08:36,679 --> 01:08:40,115
No. We've got to go now.
Just find the fuel.

721
01:08:44,086 --> 01:08:45,610
[ Gasps ]
Cari.

722
01:08:45,754 --> 01:08:46,778
What?

723
01:08:46,889 --> 01:08:48,516
-Behind you.
-[ Gasps ]

724
01:08:48,691 --> 01:08:51,455
Please. Please don't shoot.

725
01:08:52,228 --> 01:08:54,355
Don't move.

726
01:08:54,463 --> 01:08:56,431
Either of you!

727
01:08:56,599 --> 01:08:58,624
[ indistinct chanting ]

728
01:09:20,856 --> 01:09:23,290
[ Brenda gasps ]

729
01:09:25,694 --> 01:09:28,288
[ Whimpering ]

730
01:09:37,973 --> 01:09:40,498
[ Water splashing ]

731
01:09:56,292 --> 01:09:57,725
[ Chuckles ]

732
01:09:57,826 --> 01:10:00,454
[ Thunder crashes ]

733
01:10:17,179 --> 01:10:19,238
[ Footsteps approach ]

734
01:12:08,924 --> 01:12:10,255
I'm sorry. We were lost.

735
01:12:10,359 --> 01:12:12,850
And we were just trying
to find shelter.

736
01:12:13,028 --> 01:12:15,588
Trying to steal my pickup?

737
01:12:15,698 --> 01:12:17,632
That's "looking for shelter"?

738
01:12:17,800 --> 01:12:20,496
W-we didn't take anything.

739
01:12:22,171 --> 01:12:24,139
Look, if you'll just let us go,

740
01:12:24,239 --> 01:12:27,003
I promise you
we'll never bother you again.

741
01:12:27,176 --> 01:12:29,201
[ Gasping ]

742
01:12:29,311 --> 01:12:31,575
[ Groaning ]

743
01:12:37,186 --> 01:12:38,983
Cari?

744
01:12:39,154 --> 01:12:41,247
[ Groaning continues ]

745
01:12:43,425 --> 01:12:45,723
[ Gasping ]

746
01:12:49,064 --> 01:12:51,692
Cari. It's okay.

747
01:12:51,867 --> 01:12:53,835
[ Crackling ]

748
01:12:53,936 --> 01:12:55,995
[ Panting ]

749
01:13:02,945 --> 01:13:05,778
What's happening to me?

750
01:13:08,050 --> 01:13:11,042
♪ It's raining ♪

751
01:13:11,153 --> 01:13:13,747
♪ It's pouring ♪

752
01:13:13,856 --> 01:13:18,122
♪ The old man is snoring ♪

753
01:13:18,227 --> 01:13:23,426
♪ He went to bed
and bumped his head ♪

754
01:13:37,413 --> 01:13:40,348
[ Panting ]

755
01:13:41,650 --> 01:13:44,175
It's the hat.

756
01:13:46,555 --> 01:13:48,716
The hat?

757
01:13:50,025 --> 01:13:51,959
[ Sighs ]

758
01:13:52,060 --> 01:13:54,119
Go on, now, both of you.
Just get out of here.

759
01:13:54,930 --> 01:13:56,830
No.

760
01:13:56,932 --> 01:14:00,925
No. Please. Please tell me
what's going on.

761
01:14:01,103 --> 01:14:02,161
[ Sighs ]

762
01:14:02,271 --> 01:14:05,172
Your family must have been chosen
for the sacrifice.

763
01:14:05,274 --> 01:14:07,640
Chosen?
What do you mean chosen?

764
01:14:07,810 --> 01:14:10,574
Honey, you're too young to know.

765
01:14:10,679 --> 01:14:14,171
It happened well before
your parents' time.

766
01:14:15,317 --> 01:14:17,376
[ Sighs ]

767
01:14:24,493 --> 01:14:26,620
[ Lighter clicks ]

768
01:14:29,331 --> 01:14:32,391
Some 50 or so years ago...

769
01:14:32,501 --> 01:14:37,029
local farmer dug up an old hat
on his property,

770
01:14:37,139 --> 01:14:41,098
and, with it, a native curse.

771
01:14:42,344 --> 01:14:45,142
The land and the wells dried up...

772
01:14:45,247 --> 01:14:46,646
livestock all dying.

773
01:14:46,748 --> 01:14:49,148
There wasn't any food.

774
01:14:49,251 --> 01:14:50,479
Killed off half the town,

775
01:14:50,586 --> 01:14:54,750
threatened to destroy everyone
and everything in it.

776
01:14:56,058 --> 01:14:59,084
So to deal with the curse...

777
01:14:59,194 --> 01:15:01,560
the town developed a lottery.

778
01:15:01,663 --> 01:15:05,827
Choose a family
to give up three of its own,

779
01:15:05,934 --> 01:15:09,961
three children of every generation.

780
01:15:12,341 --> 01:15:14,741
Guess your family drew the lot.

781
01:15:19,882 --> 01:15:21,213
[ Cigarette butt falls ]

782
01:15:21,316 --> 01:15:23,477
[ Foot stomps ]

783
01:15:33,795 --> 01:15:35,592
[ Clang ]

784
01:15:35,697 --> 01:15:39,258
I'm sorry. I can't cure you.

785
01:15:39,368 --> 01:15:41,962
Only the rain can.

786
01:16:00,789 --> 01:16:02,154
CARI: Oh, my God.

787
01:16:12,634 --> 01:16:15,159
KYLE: Cari, come on.

788
01:16:25,547 --> 01:16:27,845
CARI: Hurry. Hurry.

789
01:16:38,694 --> 01:16:41,891
Please, please, please work.

790
01:16:43,165 --> 01:16:45,360
-[ Engine turns over ]
-KYLE: Ohh! Yes!

791
01:16:47,636 --> 01:16:49,365
Get your seat belt on.

792
01:16:54,977 --> 01:16:57,844
Shit! Shit!

793
01:17:12,194 --> 01:17:14,754
[ Groaning and coughing ]

794
01:17:14,863 --> 01:17:16,353
Who the hell is that?

795
01:17:18,467 --> 01:17:20,697
[ indistinct chanting ]

796
01:17:45,627 --> 01:17:46,821
Look at that!

797
01:17:46,928 --> 01:17:48,395
[ Panting ]

798
01:18:03,478 --> 01:18:05,207
[ Moans ]

799
01:18:06,448 --> 01:18:07,847
[ Chanting continues ]

800
01:18:09,217 --> 01:18:11,651
Cari, what's wrong?

801
01:18:11,820 --> 01:18:13,913
[ Gasping ]

802
01:18:15,524 --> 01:18:17,788
Go! Go!

803
01:18:28,704 --> 01:18:30,137
Cari, come on!

804
01:18:36,211 --> 01:18:38,236
KYLE: Open up!

805
01:18:42,417 --> 01:18:44,078
WOMAN: Come on. Come on.

806
01:18:52,828 --> 01:18:55,388
Get in there. Get in there.

807
01:19:01,236 --> 01:19:03,101
[ Pounding ]

808
01:19:03,271 --> 01:19:05,831
Ah, that ain't gonna hold.

809
01:19:05,941 --> 01:19:08,842
Here. Help me.

810
01:19:19,054 --> 01:19:21,022
[ Pounding stops ]

811
01:20:14,376 --> 01:20:15,365
Maggie?

812
01:20:18,446 --> 01:20:19,435
Aah!

813
01:20:21,416 --> 01:20:23,748
[ Sobbing ]

814
01:20:33,094 --> 01:20:35,119
Daniel.

815
01:21:13,435 --> 01:21:16,802
I am so tired, Kyle.

816
01:21:30,552 --> 01:21:32,884
[ Screams ]

817
01:21:36,191 --> 01:21:38,159
[ Growling ]

818
01:21:43,198 --> 01:21:44,859
WOMAN: Get behind me.

819
01:21:46,001 --> 01:21:47,434
[ Gun cocks ]

820
01:21:47,535 --> 01:21:49,503
I've dealt with his kind before.

821
01:22:17,766 --> 01:22:20,428
We got to help her!

822
01:22:41,790 --> 01:22:42,779
Aaaah!

823
01:23:51,259 --> 01:23:53,727
[ Water splashing ]

824
01:24:38,640 --> 01:24:41,131
Cari.

825
01:24:50,118 --> 01:24:52,951
She's getting sicker and sicker!

826
01:24:54,322 --> 01:24:56,756
Do something!

827
01:25:03,631 --> 01:25:05,496
Kyle.

828
01:25:06,501 --> 01:25:08,025
Go and get me the hat.

829
01:25:11,139 --> 01:25:13,266
But that man's out there.

830
01:25:13,441 --> 01:25:15,773
Kyle, I don't care. You run fast.

831
01:25:15,944 --> 01:25:16,740
But, Cari --

832
01:25:16,911 --> 01:25:20,108
It helped him.
Maybe it will help me.

833
01:25:24,752 --> 01:25:26,845
Kyle...

834
